T*
(Architecture overview:) Tj
T*
(HTML catalog -> normalization/section extraction -> section-aware chunking ->) Tj
T*
(BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5 embeddings -> Chroma -> retrieval + symbolic prerequisite evaluator ->) Tj
T*
(Groq-backed drafting. Symbolic logic makes the eligibility/plan decision; the LLM explains it.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Chunking / retrieval choices and tradeoffs:) Tj
T*
(Section-preserving chunks are ~800 token-equivalent units with ~120-token overlap so) Tj
T*
(prerequisite, grade, and co-requisite wording stay intact. Retrieval uses similarity search) Tj
T*
(\(k=8\) and keeps a smaller cited set for the final answer. Tradeoff: abstention cases protect) Tj
T*
(grounding but reduce overall citation coverage because unsupported questions return no claim.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Prompts / agent roles \(high level\):) Tj
T*
(Intake/Router asks clarifying questions when key profile fields are missing. Catalog Retriever) Tj
T*
(pulls evidence only. Planner/Responder combines retrieved evidence with symbolic checks to) Tj
T*
(produce prerequisite decisions or next-term plans. Verifier blocks unsupported claims and) Tj
T*
(enforces abstention when the answer is not in the catalog.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Evaluation summary: 25 queries \(10 prerequisite checks, 5 multi-hop chains, 5 program-rule,) Tj
T*
(5 not-in-docs\). Results: citation coverage 80.0%, eligibility) Tj
T*
(correctness 86.67%, abstention accuracy 100%.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key failure modes / next improvements:) Tj
T*
(The planner models major buckets well, but not the full university core or every advisor) Tj
T*
(exception path. Next steps: richer symbolic parsing for substitutions/waivers/standing,) Tj
T*
(stronger reranking, broader degree-audit coverage, and a deeper multi-term curriculum graph.) Tj
